te load-more pagination</strong>, and <strong>real-time UI updates</strong>, all written directly in Twig.</p><p>There’s no need for Vue, React, or Alpine — DataStar takes care of the reactivity by leveraging HTML attributes and a lightweight JavaScript layer. This makes it ideal for developers who want <strong>snappy, interactive experiences</strong> while keeping Craft templates fully server-rendered and easy to maintain.</p><p>Each filter or button click triggers an AJAX patch request that replaces or appends elements using Twig partials — preserving accessibility and SEO. The setup is minimal, performant, and perfectly suited for blogs, listings, or search components inside Craft CMS projects.</p><p>In short: <strong>a modern, Alpine-style experience — built purely in Twig</strong>.</p>\", \"c67defbb-160e-48ab-9dc8-7a4dc6e8db58\": \"🚀 Blog (Datastar)\"}',1,'2025-10-07 11:09:45','2025-10-07 11:09:45','ae71b49a-dbae-4d9b-89b4-45f96a17f3a0'),(644,644,1,'Home','home','__home__','{\"872f39e9-c6e7-4db6-9915-33944177d829\": \"CraftCMS Lazy —\\nA simple Craft CMS Starter Kit\"}',1,'2025-10-07 11:14:19','2025-10-07 11:14:19','dd6c1d61-2c32-42a1-a06f-b54c6bc8442f'),(645,645,1,NULL,'__temp_xmyryjgfvmihfecdlkmvkhurafqliwjajpcz',NULL,'{\"54ea783f-26e8-4a98-a119-9a041012aa68\": \"<p class=\\\"ui-teaser\\\">This starter kit is designed to help developers quickly spin up clean and maintainable Craft CMS projects. It includes ready-made examples for Matrix Blocks, CKEditor integration, and both DataStar- and Vue-powered blog listings.</p><p>This boilerplate is designed to demonstrate a clean, scalable, and modern Craft CMS setup — perfect for agencies, freelancers, and developers who want a strong starting point for new projects. Everything runs locally with DDEV, built with Vite, styled with Tailwind, and powered by real content through DataStar or Vue components.</p><h3><strong>🧩 Tech Stack</strong></h3><ul><li>🧠 <strong>Craft CMS 5</strong> – latest version with sections, Mat